messages.message: Hey, I was just using aihub-uat.internal to test the build functionality (its the first time i’ve used this deployment), and its taking me to this screen (not the new build project screen). This seems like an error. I didn’t create the empty class called Resume.
hm, there's something wrong with the sample project then

@Vasu 
Can you help take a look at build sample project ?
maybe the sample project is not where the aihub_guest user drive is

@Rakesh @Eric Han On triggering the /add_sample_project endpoint manually, it worked as expected for me. Maybe the above page was a result of an intermediate state i.e. while the indexing, modifying and copying was going on in the background, the FE sent a call to get this data, this looks something like that to me.
Adding @Aayush for inputs related to the FE.
Thanks @Vasu - can you check logs for the call yesterday by @Lee ?

Hmm, this may be caused when the sample project and the user visits the build app in the middle of processing. Wasn't sure how the build app handles processing state - we should have an intermediate state if we don't already here
